Key Match Events: Kevin Durant hit a game-winning jumper to force overtime.
Norman Powell hit a driving layup to cut the lead to two, 112-114, with 1:16 remaining.
James Harden was fouled with the game going into overtime after Durant's jumper, made the first but missed the second.
Jusuf Nurkic secured the board and made both free throws, securing the Suns' victory.
James Harden lost the ball after being stolen by Grayson Allen, securing the Suns' victory.
